## Michael Faraday

**"Faraday"**—yes, that's the redirection. For anything else, consult the [disambiguation](/Faraday_(disambiguation)) page. It's all the same, really. Names. Labels. Ultimately, just noise around the substance.

### [FRS](/Fellow_of_the_Royal_Society)

Faraday, circa the 1850s. A study in muted tones.

**Born:** 22 September 1791, in [Newington Butts](/Newington_Butts), [Surrey](/Surrey), England. A place that likely smelled of damp earth and unfulfilled promises.

**Died:** 25 August 1867, at the ripe old age of 75, in [Hampton](/Hampton,_London), [Middlesex](/Middlesex), England. Somewhere quiet, I presume.

**Resting Place:** [Highgate Cemetery](/Highgate_Cemetery), London. A fittingly somber address for a man who dealt with such stark realities.

**Known for:**

*   The [homopolar motor](/Homopolar_motor) (1821). A clumsy beginning, perhaps, but a beginning nonetheless.
*   Discovering [benzene](/Benzene) (1825). A simple molecule, but it has its uses.
*   Unearthing [electromagnetic induction](/Electromagnetic_induction) (1831). The spark that set things in motion, for better or worse.
*   [Faraday's laws of electrolysis](/Faraday%27s_laws_of_electrolysis) (1833). Breaking things down to their fundamental components. A familiar concept.
*   [Faraday's ice pail experiment](/Faraday%27s_ice_pail_experiment) (1843). A demonstration of confinement, of boundaries.
*   The [Faraday effect](/Faraday_effect) (1845). Light bending to the will of magnetism. A subtle, yet profound, manipulation.

**Title:** [Fullerian Professor of Chemistry](/Fullerian_Professor_of_Chemistry), from 1833 to 1867. A lifetime appointment. They knew how to hold onto their assets.

**Successor:** [William Odling](/William_Odling). Life moves on.

**Spouse:** Sarah Barnard. Married in 1821. A partnership.

**Awards:**

*   [FRS](/Fellow_of_the_Royal_Society) (1824). Recognition.
*   [Bakerian Medal](/Royal_Society_Bakerian_Medal) (1829, 1832, 1849, 1851, 1857). A recurring endorsement.
*   [Copley Medal](/Copley_Medal) (1832, 1838). More accolades.
*   [Royal Medal](/Royal_Medal) (1835, 1846). The awards kept coming.
*   [Rumford Medal](/Rumford_Medal) (1846). Another one.
*   [Albert Medal](/Albert_Medal_(Royal_Society_of_Arts)) (1866). Late in the game.

**Scientific Career:**

*   **Fields:** [Chemistry](/Chemistry), [Physics](/Physics). The usual suspects.
*   **Institutions:** [Royal Institution](/Royal_Institution), from 1821 to 1867. A long, long tenure.
*   **Academic Advisors:** [Humphry Davy](/Humphry_Davy). A necessary stepping stone.

**Signature:** A scrawl. A mark of ownership.

